The faint light from behind Cody was illuminating less and less of the corridor ahead, but by now, Cody was becoming used
to not being able to see more than a few feet in front of himself. “Not that I like it, mind you,” he said, giving the
darkness in front of him a halfhearted poke with the pole sickle. “Not when the darkness has a tendency to grow teeth and
lunge at you.”
